  "name": "Schottky Diode One-Way Current Demo",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "Schottky Diode One-Way Current Demo",
    "description": "The slide switch picks between two identical branches except for the Schottky orientation. West: 470Ω → red LED → Schottky (90°, forward) → ground — the LED lights. East: same chain but the Schottky is reversed (270°) — current cannot pass and the LED stays dark. A diode is a one-way valve for electricity. LEDs at 90° (anode north); forward Schottky band toward the LED."
  },
